iFirst: Lines should be 70 charactes or fewer.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iThis is indeed in the spec, and it was the impetus for my choosing		gopher.black	70
isixty-seven as the line length I use here on gopher.black. But in		gopher.black	70
igeneral a line length of 80 or fewer characters won't cause		gopher.black	70
iproblems for anyone on a desktop and a line length of 67 is still		gopher.black	70
ifar too wide to be useful on mobile. So what are we to do?		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iSome people forgo wrapping at all, assuming clients are capable of		gopher.black	70
iwrapping if they're sosphisticated. Others pick a comfortable		gopher.black	70
imiddle-ground (often 80) and stick with it half out of convenience		gopher.black	70
iand half because it's good enough. Still others who use gopher on		gopher.black	70
imobile choose to go crazy and use very narrow posts that fit those		gopher.black	70
iscreens.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iTo the spec it's wrong, but the spec doesn't have feelings. The		gopher.black	70
ispec doesn't use gopher. If someone is on their phone and very		gopher.black	70
inarrow lines make their use case better then that's absolutely the		gopher.black	70
iright call. At the end of the day it just isn't very important.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
