iSecond: misuse of type-i		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iFrom a historical perspective type i wasn't even in the spec, but		gopher.black	70
iit was already in widespread use in gopherspace within the first		gopher.black	70
iyear of its launch. Clients adjusted, use adjusted. RFC-1436[1]		gopher.black	70
inever learned to time travel, though, and remains sadly silent on		gopher.black	70
ithe topic. 		gopher.black	70
